descript.abstract: This line data layer represents hydrography for Waukesha County, Wisconsin in 2014. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Waukesha_HydroLine_2014.gdb. [The planimetric mapping product covers the entire county and was compiled at a scale of 1" = 100'. The accuracy standard used is National Map Accuracy for 1" = 100' scale mapping. The planimetric files are non-overlapping, 2-D Microstation .dgn files and are tiled by survey township.]
descript.purpose: This layer is intended for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [The planimetric maps are intended to be used as one of the base layers for overlaying with other digital layers such as cadastral features, topography and orthophotos.]
descript.supplinf: Augmented original metadata with UW-Madison specific elements. For additional information, please see original license/data sharing agreement where applicable. [The planimetric features consist of four core features. These features are pavement edges (improved and unimproved), road centerlines, water, and railroads. These features were extracted from the DTM product that was compiled as part of the Year 2000 Orthophotography project.]

overview.eaover: [The features within the digital planimetric map products are differentiated by any combination of Microstation symbology characteristics including, Level, Weight, Style and Color. All features are stored as either point, line or area features, none of which have any associated database attribution assigned. Files are structured with a naming convention of PLANttrr.dgn where tt=township, rr=range,.]
